><A HREF="gc.htm"> Of God and His Creatures</a><hr><p>
This is commonly expressed by saying that the
Blessed in heaven <i>vident Deum totum, sed non totaliter</i>.
A further illustration, suggested by Cardinal Newman's 
<i>Grammar of Assent</i>, is the case of two men both
knowing the same proposition, the one with a
'notional,' the other with a 'real' assent: only the
latter can be said fully to grasp or comprehend the
truth.

